Description:
Charm & style of Yesteryear
Under instructions from State Trustees Ltd. Laden with character and charm, this original solid brick period residence oozes future potential in this prestige residential locale. Ideally positioned in the McKinnon Secondary College Zone and within easy walking distance of Ormond station and shops.

Description:
Shops, station & spotless presentation!
Spotless, spacious and so centrally located - this is a superior start, investment or downsize opportunity! Located in a boutique group of just four, 250m from Ormond's shopping strip and station, this villa unit offers a fresh perspective with an immaculately presented two bedroom floorplan. Updated with prestige stainless-steel appliances for the classic kitchen, this pristine home features reverse-cycle air-conditioned living with a groovy stone-mantle, a dining area beside the kitchen and a super-sized fan-cooled master with a wall of robes and vanity area. Even the outdoor space is superior, with a generous wraparound courtyard accessing the garage - perfect for pets and brilliant for BBQs! Jump on the train for an easy commute, stroll to the strip for shopping and dinner, and kick around in nearby parklands...whatever you do, don't miss this superior single-level home!
large lounge, st-st app kitchen with dining, extra-large master bedrm, r/c air-con, fans, large c'yard, garage, 250m to shops & station

Liveable, loveable, affordable
Low maintenance living is the way to go in these busy times, & where better to enjoy this relaxing lifestyle than in a neat villa such as this! Fresh paintwork & new bedroom carpets add zing, while a private courtyard has ample space for a table in the sun.

Description:
Ground-floor growth potential in a leafy locale
Choose one with a gorgeous garden outlook and great growth potential! On the edge of Ormond's shopping strip and transport precinct, this sun-filled single bedroom apartment enjoys an open aspect across lawned front gardens to one of Ormond's leafiest low-traffic streets. Filled with afternoon sun, this well-presented home has living wrapping around to a classic kitchen and a garden-view bedroom with a bright ensuite bathroom. There's fitted robes for the bedroom, built-in shelving for the lounge and fan-cooling and panel-heating for added comfort. Best of all, this smart start or clever investment has a carport on title, the bus to Monash University at the end of the street and Ormond station within three blocks ... so you can add an update and grow the value in an always in-demand location!
Grnd-flr front unit with garden-view living, quality kitchen & bathrm, robes, panel heating, fan, carport, close to Monash Uni bus & station

Description:
One decked out with a pool!
Start, invest, splash out on One with a pool and a deck! Centrally located in the leafy precinct adjacent Ormond's shopping strip and station, this one bedroom apartment has a real point of difference - a place in a securely gated, rendered and refurbished group with a sparkling private pool! But that's not the only outdoor benefit, this polished apartment goes beyond a glossy interior with another added bonus - access from the bedroom to a decked outdoor area - large enough to fit a breakfast setting or BBQ. Ready to rent or enjoy with a sophisticated quality appliance kitchen, a classic black and white bathroom and glossy polished boards, this stylish apartment has intercom entry, panel heating and secure carport parking at the door. Walk to the station, stroll to the shops, dip you toes in the pool when you return...to make a splash in the rental or first-home market - this is the One!

Description:
Gracious, spacious & so well-located
Picturesque, picket-fenced and perfect for a growing family, this picture-perfect period home offers a charming blend of period grace and family space. Centrally heated and cooled with a classic kitchen overlooking family living, this abundantly accommodating home has robes and fans for every bedroom and a WIR and frameless-screened, stone-finished ensuite for the master.
But it's the expansive family living that really brings this period beauty into the modern day. In this gracious home, a charming formal sitting-room flows directly into expansive family living/dining and out through three sets of French doors to decking and sunny tank-watered gardens beyond.
Beautifully located nearby EE Gunn Reserve and Caulfield South Primary School, with Ormond shops and station within a leisurely stroll (or a last minute dash), this is gracious family living for a modern family life.

Description:
Outdoor entertainer in lifestyle location
Al fresco focused entertaining living meets a lifestyle location just a moment's walk off the Ormond restaurant and shopping strip! Offering a spacious three bedroom single-level floorplan in low-maintenance garden surrounds, this impeccable stand-alone front property is ready for you to simply move in and live the life! With a large lounge and open-plan dining supplemented by a generous panel-heated "al fresco room", this stylish home has retained many of the period art-deco features whilst delivering a modern touch with a classic Blanco kitchen featuring a servery window to the great outdoors, and a stylish black and white bathroom supplemented by a second WC in the outdoor entertaining zone. Centrally heated and surround-sound-wired inside and out, this appealing entertainer has individual climate-control units (including all bedrooms), attic storage, video intercom to secure auto-gate and built-in robes throughout. With Ormond station just around the corner it's an easy 20 minute CBD commute plus there's the bus to Monash University at the end of the street Walking distance to local schools & creches, all the boxes are ticked for easy living & entertaining in this brilliant location!
lounge, dining beside Blanco kitchen, heated al fresco room, 2nd WC, duct heating, r/c air-con, attic-store, vid-intercom, auto-gated parking

Description:
Solid, Stylish & Single-Level!
Ormond's best buy delivers designer style with a convenient lifestyle! Nestled between a front balcony & a surprisingly spacious rear private courtyard, this boutique 2 bedroom single-level unit has been artfully renovated with a stylish modern kitchen with CaesarStone benchtops, glass splashback & breakfast bar, separate laundry & a bright bathroom with double shower & bath. Light filled lounge with split system heating & air-conditioning plus rear lane access to off-street parking and a decked al fresco area, this is groovy urban living within the serenity of a largely owner-occupied group. Moments to North Road shops, cafes & restaurants & only minutes to Ormond's zone 1 station!
For more information contact Chris Hassall at Buxton Bentleigh on 0412 898 990 or the Buxton Office on 9563 9933

Description:
Original beauty from an era of size & quality!
Spotless, sizeable and so well located, this is a BIG opportunity for first home buyers, investors and empty-nesters alike. Set to the rear of a small group, this super-sized two bedroom unit dates from a time when space was plentiful, rooms were large and courtyard space wrapped right around. Immaculately maintained ever since, this up-sized unit features a large lounge, a huge kitchen with room for a dining setting, and a separate WC beyond a big laundry. Oversized double bedrooms are fitted with generous robes, the immaculate original bathroom stars solid terrazzo flooring...there's even a newish reverse-cycle air-conditioner for the living-room. Best of all, there's this perfect position with a prized Ormond address - ideal to leave the car in the garage and walk to Ormond and Glenhuntly station and the North Rd bus.
large lounge, huge eat-in kitchen, wrapround courtyard space, garage, robes, r/c air-con, walk to bus, tram & train
